        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 1:30AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 130 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Danville, or 9 miles northwest of Burlington, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oquawka, Kossuth, 4th Pumping Station Campground, West Burlington,
Kingston, Big River State Forest, Mediapolis, Starr's Cave Park and
Preserve, Sperry, Prairie Grove, Danville, Big Hollow Recreation
Area, Pleasant Grove, Ogle, Dodgeville, Beaverdale, Keithsburg,
Delabar State Park, Rozetta, and Bald Bluff.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
